00:37:25.530 --> 00:37:29.120
So like from a
supply/demand business,

00:37:29.120 --> 00:37:32.100
like the demand side was high.

00:37:32.100 --> 00:37:36.560
And we couldn't afford
to fund the trade show.

00:37:36.560 --> 00:37:40.880
So we'd bought the space,
so we leased the space

00:37:40.880 --> 00:37:43.275
with the folks that
managed those conventions.

00:37:43.275 --> 00:37:44.425
This was in Las Vegas.

00:37:44.425 --> 00:37:48.437
It's like an industry--
the American big sportswear

00:37:48.437 --> 00:37:49.270
industry trade show.

00:37:49.270 --> 00:37:51.400
It's called Magic.

00:37:51.400 --> 00:37:55.000
And so we were already on the
hook for whatever that was.

00:37:55.000 --> 00:37:58.500
But the notion of
having to fund the booth

00:37:58.500 --> 00:38:01.180
and shipping all the staff,
that option wasn't great.

00:38:01.180 --> 00:38:08.170
So we ran an audible and
we said, OK, let's just

00:38:08.170 --> 00:38:10.420
ask the industry where's Echo?

00:38:10.420 --> 00:38:11.610
So we own the booth.

00:38:11.610 --> 00:38:17.020
So our set up costs will just be
the rental fee of a red velvet

00:38:17.020 --> 00:38:20.910
rope going around the perimeter
of this oversized gargantuan

00:38:20.910 --> 00:38:22.790
booth that we really
couldn't afford.

00:38:22.790 --> 00:38:25.890
And that's one of the
reasons we were in debt.

00:38:25.890 --> 00:38:28.170
And in the middle,
there'd be a table,

00:38:28.170 --> 00:38:30.580
and there'd be a little
tea stand or whatever,

00:38:30.580 --> 00:38:32.710
and it would say "Where's
Echo," and then we

00:38:32.710 --> 00:38:37.640
proceed to run up a
risk assessment of what

00:38:37.640 --> 00:38:40.379
it would cost to basically
bomb Vegas with stickers

00:38:40.379 --> 00:38:42.045
and we paste posters
and like cardboard,

00:38:42.045 --> 00:38:43.640
real like Wu-Tang style.

00:38:43.640 --> 00:38:47.300
We just got up
everywhere in Vegas.

00:38:47.300 --> 00:38:52.470
And we took a suite
at whatever hotel,

00:38:52.470 --> 00:38:55.560
something decent
but modest budget.

00:38:55.560 --> 00:38:57.950
And that's where we
did our bookings from.

00:38:57.950 --> 00:39:01.640
And we ended up booking more
at that show-- our nonshow--

00:39:01.640 --> 00:39:04.785
than we had ever in the
history of the trade

00:39:04.785 --> 00:39:05.700
shows at that time.

00:39:05.700 --> 00:39:07.600
ROB KENNER: But the first day
was looking a little grim.

00:39:07.600 --> 00:39:08.850
MARC ECKO: It is looking grim.

00:39:08.850 --> 00:39:11.150
And it turned around,
it all turned around.

00:39:11.150 --> 00:39:13.430
And it informed our
view just generally

00:39:13.430 --> 00:39:15.890
on how to then-- cause
after you did that show,

00:39:15.890 --> 00:39:17.770
you're like we can't come back.

00:39:17.770 --> 00:39:20.500
You can't be like fuck you Magic
and then come back and then

00:39:20.500 --> 00:39:22.650
be like "we're back!"

00:39:22.650 --> 00:39:27.690
So we found one of
their Achilles heels,

00:39:27.690 --> 00:39:30.790
which was right across the
street from the convention

00:39:30.790 --> 00:39:35.120
center , there's this really--
it's kind of-- I don't want

00:39:35.120 --> 00:39:39.170
to say anything
disparaging-- and it's a bar,

00:39:39.170 --> 00:39:42.800
and we rented the
parking lot of that bar.

00:39:42.800 --> 00:39:45.840
And we put up what we call the
middle finger pavilion, which

00:39:45.840 --> 00:39:48.310
was like right in the line
of sight of the trade show

00:39:48.310 --> 00:39:52.290
and walking distance, so
we end up doing our trade

00:39:52.290 --> 00:39:54.225
shows outside of the trade show.

00:39:54.225 --> 00:39:55.850
ROB KENNER: The middle
finger pavilion.

00:39:55.850 --> 00:39:57.474
MARC ECKO: Yeah, that
was the nickname.

00:39:57.474 --> 00:39:58.660
Yeah.

00:39:58.660 --> 00:40:01.690
ROB KENNER: That's
just remarkable.

00:40:01.690 --> 00:40:03.090
Are we getting the signal?

00:40:03.090 --> 00:40:05.180
OK, well, this seems
like a great time

00:40:05.180 --> 00:40:11.750
to turn the microphones over
to those who are in attendance.

